name: Aztec restoration #12
description: From plate 40 of the 16th century Aztec Codex Laud, depicting a priest in full ceremonial dress approaching a caged owl with two sharpened bone awls in hand. An offering smokes on top of the cage. The day signs of alligator, vulture, monkey and death can be read along the bottom of the page in conjunction with the three coloured dots, signifying a date.
